  "text": "It has been suggested previously that in HMs, in addition to the CB1R-dependent retrograde signaling pathway, there exist additional mechanisms of modulation of glycinergic synaptic transmission by endocannabinoids [CITATION_1] . One of these mechanisms would be direct interaction of GlyRs and endocannabinoids. To test whether the direct modulation of the GlyR desensitization by endocannabinoids contributes to the activity-dependent changes in glycinergic transmission we performed experiments in HMs using the CB1R −/− mouse brainstem slice preparation. This model eliminates the possible impact of presynaptic retrograde modulation by endocannabinoids.",
